                    d836f28d8dc6400e9aeeffbfaf099679: '1. Increase protein intake:\n-Include more protein sources such as lean meats (chicken breast, turkey), fish, soy products, eggs, or low-fat dairy products at each meal.\n-Consider adding protein to breakfast, such as Greek yogurt, eggs, or protein powder.\n2. Balance carbohydrates:\n-Decrease intake of high-sugar foods such as desserts, sugary drinks, and refined carbohydrates (white bread, white rice).\n-Increase the intake of whole grains such as brown rice, whole wheat bread and oats, which contain more fiber and help maintain stable blood sugar.\n3. Optimize fat intake:\n-While your fat intake is normal, make sure you are consuming healthy fats such as Omega-3 fatty acids found in olive oil, nuts, and fish.\n-Reduce your intake of saturated fats and trans fats, which are commonly found in fast foods, fried foods, and processed foods.',
